Dialogue: 0,0:01:34.17,0:01:36.51,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,天气是大气的状态\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Weather is the state of an atmosphere.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:39.22,0:01:42.93,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,我们可能认为 我们作为太阳的第三行星很不理想\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}We might thinkwe've got it bad on the third planet from the Sun...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.68,0:01:48.48,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,有剧烈的雷暴\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}with vicious thunderstorms...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.65,0:01:54.02,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,炎热难当\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}oppressive heat...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.65,0:02:01.03,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,还有温度很低 有时难以忍受\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and temperatures so low, they're sometimes unbearable.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.20,0:02:07.62,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,但是 这里的天气与宇宙其他地方相比\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But weather here is a walk in the park...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.66,0:02:10.00,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,只能算小菜一碟\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}compared to weather elsewhere in the universe.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.72,0:02:24.64,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,风雨雷暴呈现出另一番奇怪的含义\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Rain, wind, and storms take on a whole new and strange meaning.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.85,0:02:29.35,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,虽然 影响这些天气事件的机制\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And while the mechanics that power these weather events...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.39,0:02:32.23,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,如地球一般高深莫测\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}are strangely similar to Earth's...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.27,0:02:35.69,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,但是 结果却难以想象\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the results are terrifying to contemplate.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.45,0:02:44.87,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,金星温度有900华氏度\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}lt's 900 degrees Fahrenheit on Venus...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.91,0:02:48.91,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,每天都如烤炉那样\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}hotter than a pizza oven every day.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.96,0:02:55.25,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,火星极其干燥 天寒地冻\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Mars is bone-dry and colder than ice-cold.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.09,0:02:59.26,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,你看到闪电\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}You've got lightning...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.93,0:03:02.51,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,你看到风暴\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}you've got storms.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.64,0:03:06.72,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,所有这些天气现象最终的成因\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}All those weather phenomena are ultimately driven...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.76,0:03:11.52,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,在于阳光不均匀照射所造成的温差\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}by the fact that the temperature differences...created by uneven input of sunlight...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.56,0:03:14.35,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,引起的大气运动\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}are going to cause motions in the atmosphere.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.24,0:03:22.99,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,或许地球的最终命运的答案\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Perhaps the answers to Earth's ultimate fate...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.03,0:03:25.66,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,就在这巨大的太空之谜中\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}lie in the great unknown of space.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.74,0:03:32.33,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,我们来拍点一下宇宙所提供的最极端的天气\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And we are counting down the most extreme weather...the universe has to offer.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.58,0:03:37.25,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,你想了解我们星球的气候可能的转变途径吗？\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}You want to learn about which way our planet can turn climatically?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.30,0:03:44.55,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,那就看一下我们太阳系里的邻近星球吧\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Have a look at some neighboring planets...within our own solar system.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.47,0:03:54.23,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,科学家知道所有天气都始于一样东西:热\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Scientists know all weather starts with one thing: Heat.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.27,0:03:57.11,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,热是创造风的媒介\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Heat is a catalyst that creates winds.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.16,0:04:05.86,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,其它行星上的风\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And there are winds on other planets...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.91,0:04:08.66,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,完全不同于地球母亲所遇到过的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}unlike anything Mother Earth has ever seen.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.67,0:04:22.80,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,木星是颗巨大的行星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Jupiter is a monster planet.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.84,0:04:25.05,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,如果你将所有的行星加在一起\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}lfyou add up all the planets together...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.09,0:04:28.97,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,还够不上这颗叫做木星的巨大行星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}theywould not total the gigantic planet called Jupiter.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.77,0:04:33.35,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,木星是行星游乐园\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Jupiter is the planetary amusement park...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.39,0:04:35.39,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,在提及大风的天气时\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}when it comes to windy conditions.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.98,0:04:41.36,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,木星上的高空气流很酷\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Jet streams on Jupiter are pretty cool.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.07,0:04:43.99,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,在地球上 大约说来\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Here on Earth, we, roughly speaking...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.03,0:04:45.74,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,在南北半球各有一条高空气流\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}have about onejet stream per hemisphere.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.45,0:04:48.45,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,木星就不一样了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Jupiter's different.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.49,0:04:50.49,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,木星大约有30条高空气流\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Jupiter has about thirtyjet streams.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.54,0:04:54.87,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,它们都与云带结合在一起\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}These are associated with the cloud bands.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.96,0:04:59.67,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,木星的气流环绕着星球\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Jupiter"sjet streams rip around the planet...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.71,0:05:01.71,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,反方向行进\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}running in opposite directions.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.01,0:05:08.01,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,通过其表面不同的颜色来界定\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Defined by different colors invisible on its surface...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.05,0:05:09.85,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,这些气流四处奔忙于\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}thesejet streams tear around...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.89,0:05:13.39,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,木星厚达1000英里的大气层里\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Jupiter"s astounding 1,000-mile-thick atmosphere.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.52,0:05:19.69,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,地球 相比之下 只有一点点高空气流\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Earth, in comparison, has only a fewjet streams...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.73,0:05:22.69,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,大气层也只有100英里厚\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and an atmosphere only100 miles thick.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.90,0:05:30.62,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,但是 为何或有这么多的气流 为何风肆虐这颗星球\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But why so manyjet streams, and why winds at all on a planet...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.66,0:05:33.66,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,而它得到的阳光甚至只有地球的四分之一\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that doesn't even get a quarter ofthe sunlight as Earth?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.46,0:05:42.84,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,一种理论认为这些风是\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}One theory suggests these winds are a direct result...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.88,0:05:46.21,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,这颗热行星正在自我冷却的直接结果\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}ofthis hot planet just trying to cool itself off.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.59,0:05:50.47,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,木星是颗大行星 质量超过地球300多倍\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Jupiter is a huge planet, over 300 Earth masses.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.51,0:05:52.89,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,其形成伴随着大量的热\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And it formed with a huge, huge amount of heat.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.89,0:05:58.31,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,它个头之大以至于它还在努力摆脱这种生成热\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And it's so big that it's still trying to get rid of this heat offormation.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.15,0:06:04.40,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,这种持续的热释放缓慢地上升到了木星的大气层里\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}This constant release of heat slowly rises into Jupiter"s atmosphere...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.44,0:06:06.11,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,遭遇到了冷空气\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and collides with cooler air.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.49,0:06:12.95,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,和地球一样 她需要平衡冷暖气流\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Like Earth and her need to balance hot and cold streams of air...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.99,0:06:14.91,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,在高低压系统中\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}in high and low-pressure systems...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.95,0:06:17.62,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,木星也在为常态而抗争\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Jupiter also struggles for normalcy.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.54,0:06:25.67,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,能量带一直以来驱动着木星大气层\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}That energy band is used to drive the various storms and winds...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.71,0:06:27.71,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,上部的风暴和气流\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}in the upper atmosphere of Jupiter.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.10,0:06:35.10,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,木星的气流实在凶猛\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Thejet streams on Jupiter are really ferocious.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.14,0:06:37.81,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,其时速达到数百英里\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}They go at several hundred miles per hour...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.85,0:06:42.31,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,大量气体压缩在气流中\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and there's a lot of gas zipping along this stream.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.36,0:06:46.19,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,但是完全不同于地球上相当稳定的气流\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But unlike on Earth, thejet streams are pretty stable.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.86,0:06:53.24,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,地球上 很少见到地面风有超过时速200英里的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}On Earth, it's rare for surface winds...to reach over 200 miles per hour.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.28,0:06:55.12,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,木星上的气流的速度\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Jet streams on Jupiter reach speeds...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.16,0:06:57.83,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,居然高达时速300英里\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}exceeding up to about 300 miles per hour.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.42,0:07:03.29,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,真是太快了 你都迈不出步了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}That's really fast. And you can't get out.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.33,0:07:04.79,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,你会被困在气流之中\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}You're trapped inside thejet stream.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.55,0:07:09.38,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,穿行木星的赤道气流\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Traveling through Jupiter's equatorial jet stream...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.42,0:07:12.09,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,就像是驾乘地狱过山车\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}would be like a roller coaster ride from hell.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.14,0:07:16.68,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,就像是这个永不停止 永无尽头的过山车\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}lt's like this continuous, never-ending roller coaster ride.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.72,0:07:17.76,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,我好喜欢啊\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}l love it!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.94,0:07:25.02,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,好刺激啊\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}What a thrill!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.06,0:07:29.07,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,你会被抛上甩下上百英里\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}You would be pushed up and down by up to a hundred miles.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.07,0:07:34.99,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,厉害\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}- This is huge. - Oh, man.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.03,0:07:37.58,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,其引起的压力变化远大于\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}lt would lead to a much greater change in pressure...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.62,0:07:40.37,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,从地面登上珠穆朗玛峰顶\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}than going from the Earth's surface up to the top of Mount Everest.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.80,0:07:51.38,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,木星的气流叹为观止\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Jupiter'sjet streams are pretty impressive...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.42,0:07:55.30,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,但是 300英里时速与我们下一颗行星相比可谓小巫见大巫了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}but 300 miles per hour is nothing compared to our next planet.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.11,0:08:09.73,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,乍一看 海王星是最后的地方\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}At first glance, Neptune is the last place...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.78,0:08:13.90,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,科学家预计会发现狂暴的天气 更不用提狂风大作了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}scientists expect to find wild weather, let alone vicious winds.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.95,0:08:19.49,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,这个冰冷的星球上热并不充分\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Heat is not in abundance on this chilly planet.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.54,0:08:22.54,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,海王星极度寒冷\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Neptune is frigid, frigid cold.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.58,0:08:26.25,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,海王星所吸收的阳光只有地球的0.1%\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Neptune only absorbs 0.1 percent ofthe sunlight that Earth does.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.67,0:08:35.51,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,1989年之前 海王星一直被认为是极其乏味的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Up until 1989, Neptune was considered, well, boring.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.68,0:08:42.22,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,远离太阳 拥有一个165年的运行轨道\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Sitting far away from the Sun and having an orbit of165 years...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.27,0:08:45.85,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,科学家并不认为这颗蓝色星球上会有多少发现\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}scientists didn't believe much was to be discovered on the blue planet.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.81,0:08:52.03,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,航海者2号的造访改变了一切\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}A visit from Voyager ll changed all that.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.54,0:09:03.75,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,在航天器掠过这颗行星时\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}As the orbiter zoomed past the planet...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.79,0:09:07.75,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,科学家被发现的云的踪迹惊呆了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}scientists were shocked to discover traces of clouds.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.92,0:09:13.34,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,最为惊讶的是 这些云围绕海王星的速度\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Most surprising, these clouds were traveling around Neptune...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.38,0:09:15.51,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,难以置信\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}at ferocious speeds.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.55,0:09:17.59,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,有东西在裹挟着它们\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Something was carrying them.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.64,0:09:20.93,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,是风吗 离太阳这么远？\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But wind, so far away from the Sun?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.97,0:09:23.97,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,海王星是太阳系里风力最大的行星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Neptune is the windiest planet in the solar system.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.90,0:09:32.48,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,海王星表面的风超过时速1000英里\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Winds blow on the surface of Neptune over1,000 miles per hour.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.03,0:09:38.78,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,设想一下 突破了声障\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}lmagine that, breaking the sound barrier...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.82,0:09:42.53,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,你随时一看 风就呼啸而过\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}every time you simply look up and the winds blow past you.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.37,0:09:50.96,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,科学家估计风速高达每小时1500英里\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Scientists estimate winds reach up to 1,500 miles per hour...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.00,0:09:54.09,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,取决于天气条件和风暴的发展\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}depending on weather conditions and storms that develop.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.68,0:09:59.93,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,我们太阳系里一个重大之谜\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}A major unsolved puzzle in our solar system...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.97,0:10:02.10,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,事实上就是海王星的风速\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}is the fact that the wind speeds on Neptune...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.14,0:10:04.35,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,居然超过了木星的风速\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}are actually much faster than those on Jupiter...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.39,0:10:05.81,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,尽管 事实上 海王星接收的阳光\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}despite the fact that Neptune receives...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.85,0:10:09.89,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,或许只有木星的4%\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}only maybe four percent of the sunlight that Jupiter does.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.44,0:10:13.57,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,这种阳光或热的贫乏\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}This lack of sunlight or heat...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.61,0:10:15.94,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,完全违背了科学家所知道的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}completely contradicts what scientists know...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.99,0:10:18.32,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,地球上风的形成规律\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}about howwinds develop here on Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.20,0:10:22.82,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,你可能会认为阳光越强\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}You might think that the stronger the sunlight...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.87,0:10:24.16,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,风也会越强\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the stronger the winds would be.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.20,0:10:27.45,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,在将地球与海王星相提并论时 这显然是不对的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}This is obviously not true when comparing Earth to Neptune...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.50,0:10:30.79,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,因为 地球上的风通常时速30英里\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}since Earth's winds are typically maybe thirty miles per hour...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.83,0:10:33.42,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,然而 海王星的风速高达每小时900英里\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}whereas those on Neptune reach 900 miles per hour.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.30,0:10:42.34,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,科学家怀疑内部存在热\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Scientists suspect there is internal heat left over...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.39,0:10:46.26,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,是海王星在几十亿年前形成时残留的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}from Neptune's formation billions ofyears ago...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.31,0:10:48.48,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,但是 困惑的是 这个内部的热怎么会\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}but are perplexed how this internal heat...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.52,0:10:51.14,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,足够以这样的速度来推动风的呢？\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}could be enough to drive winds to this speed.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.73,0:10:58.94,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,海王星释放的热是太阳投入的两倍\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}There's twice as much heat getting out of Neptune...as what the Sun is putting in.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.99,0:11:03.74,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,可是 这还不足以解释海王星上的巨风\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}However, that's not enough to explain the tremendous winds of Neptune.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.62,0:11:12.62,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,科学已经提出了另一个有关海王星狂风的假设\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And science has come up with another hypothesis...for Neptune's racing winds.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.67,0:11:15.34,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,缺少摩擦可能会让这些风\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}A lack offriction might allow these winds...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.38,0:11:18.59,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,围绕着星球畅通无阻\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to fly uninhibited around the planet.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.63,0:11:21.97,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,我们要十分感谢地球存在着摩擦\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}We can be very thankful that there's friction on Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.43,0:11:28.72,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,摩擦来自风击打树木和建筑这样的东西\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Friction comes about when the winds...are banging into things like trees and buildings...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.77,0:11:30.64,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,以及山峦这样的地形\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and terrain like mountains...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.02,0:11:34.81,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,所以摩擦最终会减缓风速\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}so friction ends up slowing down the winds.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.28,0:11:43.11,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,和其它气体巨星一样 海王星没有固体表面\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Like other gas giants, Neptune has no solid surface.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.57,0:11:46.78,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,即使阳光非常微弱\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Even though the sunlight is extremelyweak...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.83,0:11:49.24,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,只要摩擦也非常微弱\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}ifthe friction is also extremely weak...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.29,0:11:51.62,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,那么你就可以随着时间的推移积累成极快的风速\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}then you can build up very fast winds over time.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.50,0:11:59.63,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,海王星的风是太阳系里最引人注目的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Neptune's winds are the most impressive in our solar system...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.38,0:12:03.72,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,但是宇宙可是个大地方啊\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}but the universe is a big place.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.76,0:12:06.80,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,这里的冠军与外太空的天气相比\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And what is a champion here pales in comparison...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.85,0:12:09.51,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,就相形见绌了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to weatherfurther out in space.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.02,0:12:18.61,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,或许行星科学上最激动人心的发现\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Perhaps the most exciting discovery in planetary science...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.65,0:12:22.90,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,就是最令人乍舌的风 那是我们指望永远不要体验的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}are the most amazing winds we could hope to never experience.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.62,0:12:35.46,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,如果你想体验宇宙间最狂野的风\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}lfyou want to experience the wildest winds in the cosmos...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.50,0:12:39.29,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,那么热木星就是你的终点了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}then hot Jupiters are your destination.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.34,0:12:42.17,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,热木星属于日外行星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Hot Jupiters are a class of exoplanets.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.64,0:12:49.47,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,它肯定不是你想去的地方\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}lt's definitely not a place you want to be.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.51,0:12:51.06,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,它比海王星要糟糕上好多好多\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}lt's much, much worse than Neptune.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.10,0:12:52.68,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,温度高上好多 风要快上好多\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}lt's much hotter. The winds are much faster.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.73,0:12:56.10,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,所以 你想找块平静之地来开张营业的话\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}So, ifyou want a nice kind of calm place to set up shop...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.15,0:12:57.65,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,你或许会相中海王星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}you'd probably be better off going with Neptune.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.69,0:13:00.40,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,这些家伙肯定都是糟透了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}These guys are definitely much, much worse.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.57,0:13:05.57,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,热木星紧紧围绕着自己的母星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Hot Jupiters orbit tightly around their stars...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.61,0:13:08.28,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,比水星距离太阳还要近\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}far closer than Mercury to our own Sun.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.41,0:13:14.79,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,以至于酷热导致了某些狂野的天气\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And all that intense heat makes for some wild weather.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.46,0:13:21.84,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,作为比较 其从母星那里接受的阳光2万倍于\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}For comparison, it gets about 20,000 times more light...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.88,0:13:24.17,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,木星从太阳所接受的阳光\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}from its star than Jupiter does from the Sun.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.26,0:13:27.09,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,这些行星的温度极高\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The temperatures on these planets are enormous...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.13,0:13:31.51,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,介于1500至2000华氏度之间 甚至更高\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}between 1,500 and 2,000 degrees Fahrenheit or more.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.64,0:13:37.02,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,有些热木星被潮汐锁定\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Some hot Jupiters are tidally locked...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.06,0:13:40.23,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,引力效应使得它们始终将自己的一面\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}a gravitational effect that leads them to show the same face...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.27,0:13:42.27,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,露给自己的母星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to their star at all times.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.07,0:13:47.32,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,你看到这个行星的一面\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}You've got one side of this planet...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.36,0:13:50.37,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,始终受到其母星的阳光的煎熬\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that's being just blasted with light from the star all the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.41,0:13:52.99,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,所以你可以料到那里非常非常的热\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}So you would expect that to be very, very hot.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.04,0:13:55.41,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,然而 同时 你可以看到这颗行星的阴影面\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But at the same time, you've got this night side ofthe planet...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.45,0:13:58.08,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,从不见母星的丝毫阳光\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that never sees any light from the star.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.12,0:14:01.92,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,所以 要知道 或许那阴影面其实是非常寒冷的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}So, you know, perhaps that night side is actually quite cold.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.09,0:14:07.13,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,为获得热木星的温度\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Taking hot Jupiters' temperatures...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.17,0:14:10.26,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,科学家测量了行星在经过其前面遮挡\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}scientists measured how much light is eclipsed from the planet...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.30,0:14:15.10,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,以及在其背后所产生的光\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}as it passes in front of and behind its star during its orbit.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.14,0:14:18.73,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,它们实际上在红外光波上相对强一些\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}So they actually glow relatively brightly at infrared wavelength.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.65,0:14:24.02,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,因此 你想获得行星的温度\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}So ifyou want to take the temperature of a planet...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.07,0:14:25.65,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,你就要获得这些红外波长\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}you want to look at these infrared wavelengths.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.69,0:14:27.53,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,你要测量它们发出的热\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}You want to measure the heat that they're giving off.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.82,0:14:33.41,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,但是 日照面与阴影面之间的温差\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But the temperature difference...between the day side and night side...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.45,0:14:34.83,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,实际上没什么差异\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}is virtually the same.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.87,0:14:39.46,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,就极端状况而言 这是不可思议的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}This was astounding, considering the extreme situation.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.46,0:14:45.17,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,有东西在将热从日照面传递到阴影面\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Something was transferring the heat...from the day side to the night side.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.21,0:14:46.21,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,那是什么呢？\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But what?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.09,0:14:52.80,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,惊人的风速就是答案\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Winds traveling at amazing speeds were the answer.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.60,0:14:55.10,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,因此 我们的模型告诉我们\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And so our models tell us...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.14,0:14:58.60,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,风速有可能达到每小时6000英里\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that the winds could be as fast as maybe 6,000 miles per hour.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.64,0:15:01.60,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,推测某些热木星上有时速6000英里的风速\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The 6,000-mile-per-hourwinds inferred on some hot Jupiters...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.65,0:15:05.02,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,远超过我们太阳系里已知的所有风速\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}is much faster than any winds that we know of in our solar system.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.69,0:15:09.78,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,时速6000英里有多快？\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Howfast is 6,000 miles per hour?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.82,0:15:11.65,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,以那样的速度 你可以在20分钟里\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}At that speed, you could travel...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.70,0:15:14.70,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,从纽约抵达洛杉矶\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}fom NewYork to Los Angeles in twenty minutes.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.49,0:15:19.66,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,你看到了温度高得惊人的日照面\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}You've got this incredibly hot day side.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.71,0:15:22.25,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,你看到所有高温气体产生于日照面\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And so you've got all this hot gas sitting there on the day side...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.29,0:15:25.63,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,好像它应该会快速地流向阴影面\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and sort ofwhat it wants to do...is to kind of go rushing around to the night side.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.34,0:15:29.13,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,热气体产生的风\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Winds are created by hot air...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.17,0:15:32.80,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,应该会流向行星的阴影面\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}wanting to travel to the cold side of the planet.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.84,0:15:35.22,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,所以说有点像冲浪风帆\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}So it's a little bit like a windsurfer.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.72,0:15:39.31,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,如果你来这里碰上刮风天 竖起风帆\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}lfyou come out here on a windy day and you put your sail up...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.35,0:15:40.43,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,就可以赶上理想的风\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}you can really catch a good breeze...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.48,0:15:42.60,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,就可以在港口驰骋了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and you can go flying across the harbor.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.94,0:15:46.15,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,那些行星的状况也一样\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}lt's the same thing with these planets.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.19,0:15:48.27,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,你遇上惊人的强风\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}You have such incredibly strong winds...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.32,0:15:49.82,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,它们搭上气体的便车\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that they can really just pick that gas up...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.86,0:15:51.49,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,一路横扫到阴影面\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and whip it all the way around to the night side...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.53,0:15:53.74,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,直到整个冷却下来\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}before it even cools off at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.70,0:15:57.08,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,很难驾驭那样的天气的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}lt's hard to beat weather like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.12,0:15:58.41,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,时速6000英里的风\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Six thousand-mile-an-hourwinds...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.45,0:16:00.45,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,你碰上这样的行星会如痴如醉的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}is about as crazy as you can get with a planet.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.37,0:16:06.38,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,在提及太空中的天气时\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Scientists have learned to expect the unexpected...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.42,0:16:08.75,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,科学家已感到出乎意料\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}when it comes to weather in space.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.38,0:16:17.85,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,有时风会变成龙卷风那样的风暴\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Sometimes winds become storms like tornadoes.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.89,0:16:20.60,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,星际龙卷风变幻莫测\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And galactic tornadoes are unpredictable...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.64,0:16:23.14,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,其行动相当诡异\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and behave in ratherweird ways.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.40,0:16:37.24,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,最近一个规模宏大的龙卷风在太空中发现了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Recently, a tornado of epic proportions was discovered in space.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.75,0:16:45.12,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,这个太空龙卷风就是赫比格 - 哈罗天体\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}This space tornado is a Herbig-Haro object...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.17,0:16:48.96,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,是一颗正在形成的恒星产生的风创造出来\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}created by winds as the result of a forming star.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.96,0:16:55.47,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,赫比格 - 哈罗天体是一个发光的气体云\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}A Herbig-Haro object is a glowing cloud of gas...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.93,0:17:01.68,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,是高速喷射的气体\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}produced when a high-speed jet of gas...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.72,0:17:06.31,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,猛击周围静止的气体时生成的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}smashes into surrounding, essentially, stationary gas.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.48,0:17:10.77,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,这个高速射流加热静止的气体\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}So this high-speed jet heats the stationary gas...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.82,0:17:12.48,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,使其发光\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and causes it to glow.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.16,0:17:21.74,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,这个天体不费吹灰之力就坐上了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}This object would easily be number one...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.79,0:17:24.75,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,宇宙间最猛烈龙卷风的头把交椅\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}on the list ofwildest tornadoes in the universe...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.79,0:17:28.21,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,出了一个重要的事实\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}except for one important fact.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.25,0:17:30.42,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,它其实不是龙卷风\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}lt's not actually a tornado.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.46,0:17:32.63,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,其形状与龙卷风并无二异\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}lts shape is very suggestive of a tornado.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.63,0:17:35.59,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,它具有螺旋状\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}lt has this helical shape to it...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.63,0:17:37.30,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,看上去一路盘旋\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that looks like it is twisting along...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.34,0:17:41.22,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,但是它其实并不是龙卷风那样的旋转物体\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}but it's actually not a rotating object like a tornado.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.68,0:17:45.39,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,并不像地球上的龙卷风那样\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Unlike a tornado on Earth...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.43,0:17:48.56,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,旋风创造出一个漏斗状\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}where a vortex ofwind creates a conical shape...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.60,0:17:51.44,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,这个由磁力产生的龙卷风\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}this tornado is created by magnetic forces...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.48,0:17:54.15,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,正在创作宇宙尘埃粒子的尾流\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}creating a wake of cosmic dust and particles.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.65,0:18:00.16,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,这东西里面好像呈现出螺旋状\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}This one appears to have sort of a spiral shape within it.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.20,0:18:03.08,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,那确实有点怪异 因为其它大多数\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And that's really kind ofweird because most of the others...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.12,0:18:05.66,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,确实没有螺旋状\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}really don't have the spiral pattern.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.12,0:18:13.04,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,不过旋转的原因或许有别于地球上的龙卷风\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But the cause of the spin is probably different...from that of a tornado on Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.55,0:18:21.80,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,星际龙卷风的亚军\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Number two on the galactic tornado list...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.85,0:18:24.76,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,更像我们在地球上所看到的龙卷风\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}is much more like tornadoes we find at home...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.81,0:18:27.48,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,它高高地矗立着\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and it's a towering presence.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.65,0:18:36.07,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,它们被称为尘暴\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}They're called dust devils...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.11,0:18:40.03,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,它们是火星对星际龙卷风的回应\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and they are Mars' answer to a planetary tornado.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.50,0:18:48.33,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,火星上的尘暴很酷\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Dust storms on Mars are pretty cool.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.37,0:18:52.13,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,每个火星年都会发生数千个风暴\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}There are thousands of local storms that occur every Mars year...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.17,0:18:54.09,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,引发了昏暗的尘埃云\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}meaning dust clouds that are opaque...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.13,0:18:56.38,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,或许会穿越数十乃至数百英里\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and maybe tens to hundreds of miles across...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.42,0:18:57.71,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,会有几英里高\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and a few miles tall.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.76,0:19:01.22,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,通常一说起红色星球\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Often referred to as the Red Planet...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.26,0:19:05.01,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,火星就是个尘土飞扬的荒漠之地\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Mars is a dusty and dismal place.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.06,0:19:08.22,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,其表面覆盖着沙层\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}lts surface is covered by sand.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.27,0:19:11.27,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,很显然 其表面没有液态水\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Apparently, there is no liquid water on the surface.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.90,0:19:17.98,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,在这个尘土飞扬的地区 太阳一旦升起 麻烦也就开始了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And in this dusty terrain, when the Sun rises, trouble starts.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.65,0:19:23.03,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,尘暴可以宽达数百码\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Dust devils can be hundreds ofyards wide...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.07,0:19:24.99,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,半英里甚至更高\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and half a mile or more tall...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.03,0:19:28.33,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,以时速70英里盘旋扫过地表\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}spinning seventy miles an hour across the surface...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.37,0:19:32.71,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,它们可是地球龙卷风的同类\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and they have similarities to Earth's own tornadoes.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.75,0:19:35.54,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,至于尘暴里的基本力量\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}As far as the basic forces inside a dust devil...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.59,0:19:37.59,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,非常类似于龙卷风里的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}they're pretty similar to in a tornado.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.63,0:19:42.30,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,两者都是在细长的漩涡里 在低压中心\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}They're both thin vortices that rotate and are low-pressure centers.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.34,0:19:44.55,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,然而 龙卷风要强烈得多得多\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Yet a tornado is much, much stronger...
