Dialogue: 0,0:26:12.36,0:26:13.94,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,这些有毒降雨\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And these toxic rains...
Dialogue: 0,0:26:13.98,0:26:17.32,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,是你在太空中所见到的最糟糕的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}are some of the worst you'll find anywhere in space.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:29.04,0:26:31.42,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,远远经过土星之环\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Far out past the rings of Saturn...
Dialogue: 0,0:26:31.46,0:26:34.17,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,有一颗太阳系里第二大的卫星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}lies the second biggest moon in the solar system...
Dialogue: 0,0:26:41.18,0:26:42.34,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,土卫六\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Titan.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:47.85,0:26:52.98,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,2005年 卡西尼-惠更斯探测器穿越土卫六的大气层\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}ln 2005, the Huygens-Cassini probe pierced Titan's atmosphere...
Dialogue: 0,0:26:53.02,0:26:54.82,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,登陆其表面\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}landing on its surface.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:59.11,0:27:03.49,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,发现那是个地貌与地球极为相似的地方\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}What it discovered was a place with features eerily similar to Earth's.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:07.75,0:27:11.29,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,土卫六是太阳系里唯一一个行星体\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Titan is the only planetary body in the solar system...
Dialogue: 0,0:27:11.33,0:27:13.71,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,具有类似地球的海洋\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that has seas like Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:14.88,0:27:19.01,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,事实上 我把土卫六看作是疯狂版的地球\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}ln fact, l regard Titan as a deranged version of Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:19.05,0:27:23.14,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,科学家兴奋地发现有山有水\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Scientists were excited to discover mountains, washes...
Dialogue: 0,0:27:23.18,0:27:25.93,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,甚至苏必利尔湖大小的湖泊\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}even lakes the size of Lake Superior.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:28.85,0:27:32.73,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,土卫六 江河湖海中的液体不是水\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And the liquid that fills Titan's lakes and rivers isn't water.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:37.15,0:27:38.78,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,而是甲烷\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}lt's methane.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:38.82,0:27:40.49,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,我可不想去那些湖里游泳\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}l wouldn't want to go swimming in one ofthose lakes.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:40.53,0:27:43.11,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,那是液态甲烷 极其寒冷\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}They're liquid methane, which is extraordinarily cold.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:45.74,0:27:48.99,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,那就意味着一旦冷凝发生在这个星球上\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And that means when condensation occurs on this planet...
Dialogue: 0,0:27:49.04,0:27:50.83,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,就会降下甲烷\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}it rains methane.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:57.21,0:28:00.26,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,土卫六的降雨不是每天都会发生的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Rain on Titan isn't an everyday occurrence.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:04.34,0:28:08.01,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,事实上 科学家也只看到了没几次云的形成\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}ln fact, scientists have only witnessed cloud formation a few times.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:10.68,0:28:14.06,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,但是 证据比比皆是\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But the evidence is everywhere...
Dialogue: 0,0:28:14.10,0:28:17.94,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,深度冲刷是大范围降雨的结果\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}deep washes as a result of significant rainfall.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:19.40,0:28:20.61,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,这里是图森\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Here we are in Tucson.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:20.65,0:28:23.11,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,这里好多天没下雨了 通常不下雨\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}lt hasn't rained for days, and it doesn't usually rain...
Dialogue: 0,0:28:23.15,0:28:25.32,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,但是偶尔会下很大的雨\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}but, occasionally, it rains very strong...
Dialogue: 0,0:28:25.37,0:28:28.62,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,我们可以看到有大量的水冲刷这里\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and we get a lot ofwater coming through this wash...
Dialogue: 0,0:28:28.66,0:28:31.12,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,侵蚀这堵墙\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and eroding this wall.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:31.16,0:28:34.83,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,我们在土卫六看到同样的证据\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}This is the same kind of evidence we see on Titan...
Dialogue: 0,0:28:38.63,0:28:40.25,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,那里通常不下雨\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}where usually it doesn't rain...
Dialogue: 0,0:28:40.30,0:28:44.05,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,但是 偶尔 会造成惊人的冲刷\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}but, occasionally, it produces phenomenal washes.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:46.39,0:28:48.93,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,土卫六的暴雨可能非常厉害\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Rainstorms on Titan might be pretty violent.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:48.97,0:28:51.60,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,我们看到地表有大量的侵蚀痕迹\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}We see lots of erosional patterns on the surface...
Dialogue: 0,0:28:51.64,0:28:54.23,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,那表明一些暴雨是相当的强劲\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that suggest that some of these storms...have been pretty powerful.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:56.23,0:29:00.23,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,科学家认为土卫六上的风暴的发展需要时间\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Scientists believe it takes time for a storm to develop on Titan.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:01.69,0:29:06.24,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,偶尔 大量的云会堆积起来形成暴雨\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And every once in a while, enough clouds build so a rainstorm occurs.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:07.66,0:29:10.33,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,那么我们真看到风暴又会如何呢？\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}So what ifwe do see a storm here?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:10.37,0:29:11.95,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,会是什么样子的呢？\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}What would it look like?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:12.00,0:29:14.04,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,大到不可思议\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Well, the big ones are incredible.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:14.08,0:29:17.21,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,它们会覆盖整个天空 从这头到那一头\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Theywould cover the sky from one end to the next...
Dialogue: 0,0:29:17.25,0:29:22.42,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,我们会看到和风细雨从天而降\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and we would eventually start seeing these very gently falling drops...
Dialogue: 0,0:29:22.46,0:29:25.55,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,要比我们在地球上看到的缓和多了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}much slower than the rain that we have on Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:25.59,0:29:27.93,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,事实上 整个看上去似乎是慢动作\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}ln fact, everything would seem to be in slow motion.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:27.97,0:29:30.18,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,风会比较柔和\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The winds would be a little bit slower...
Dialogue: 0,0:29:30.22,0:29:34.35,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,雨滴缓缓落下 那可不是水\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and the drops would gently land, and theywouldn't be water.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:34.39,0:29:37.06,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,它们可是天然气\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}They would be natural gas.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:39.36,0:29:44.69,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,想象一下 有毒的黏稠原油细雨\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}lmagine a toxic drizzle with the consistency ofwaxy crude oil...
Dialogue: 0,0:29:44.74,0:29:47.36,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,一直是零下300度\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}all at minus 300 degrees.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:50.33,0:29:51.49,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,那就是土卫六\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}That's Titan.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:11.39,0:30:13.85,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,回到金星上 从来就不存在问题\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Back on Venus, there's never an issue...
Dialogue: 0,0:30:13.89,0:30:16.60,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,因为太阳提供着足够的热量\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}with getting enough heat from the Sun.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:16.64,0:30:20.10,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,由于 二氧化碳永远被困在大气层里\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}With carbon dioxide forever trapped in the atmosphere...
Dialogue: 0,0:30:20.15,0:30:23.07,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,其温室效应已经失控了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}it has a greenhouse effect gone wild.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:26.44,0:30:30.07,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,已经到了热产生了冷凝云\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}All that heat creates condensation and clouds...
Dialogue: 0,0:30:33.70,0:30:35.37,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,充满了硫酸\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}thick with sulfuric acid.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:38.00,0:30:39.21,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,真是个讽刺\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Here's the irony.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:39.25,0:30:42.38,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,金星是以美的女神命名的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Venus is named for the goddess of beauty.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:42.42,0:30:49.59,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,美丽金星的源头居然是科学上最出名的酸之一\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The source of the beauty ofVenus...is one of the most potent acids known to science.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:49.63,0:30:52.76,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,换句话说 女性并不是来自金星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}ln otherwords, women are not from Venus.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:54.26,0:30:58.06,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,那里好像风暴和对流一刻不停\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}There seem to be storms and convection patterns that move around.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:00.90,0:31:03.90,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,云层里到处都是一片动荡\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}There are places within those clouds...that are very turbulent.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:06.65,0:31:10.36,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,金星的暴雨发生在离地30英里处\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Rainstorms on Venus happen thirty miles up from the surface...
Dialogue: 0,0:31:10.41,0:31:15.95,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,云层底部 持续下着酸雨\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}in the cloud beds, and acid rain falls constantly.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:17.58,0:31:21.12,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,金星的酸雨实际上确确实实是电池酸液\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The thing about the acid rain on Venus...is that it literally is battery acid.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:21.17,0:31:27.71,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,非常强 那酸会腐蚀皮肤 危害极大\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}lt's so strong, that acid...that it would eat through skin and do very nasty things.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:27.76,0:31:30.01,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,所以 不管你身体的什么部位\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}So whatever's left ofyour body...
Dialogue: 0,0:31:30.05,0:31:34.60,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,都会被硫酸烧成灰烬\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}would be burnt into a charred piece of powder...by the sulfuric acid.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:37.47,0:31:39.56,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,然而最后盘点的雨\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But the final rain on the countdown...
Dialogue: 0,0:31:39.60,0:31:44.48,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,是最最有毒的 或许就是最危险的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}is the most toxic, if not the most dangerous of all.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:52.82,0:31:56.33,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,宇宙间 失败的恒星 即所谓的褐矮星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Throughout the universe, failed stars, called brown dwarfs...
Dialogue: 0,0:31:56.37,0:31:58.20,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,隐藏在暗处\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}hide in the shadows.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:00.75,0:32:03.83,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,虽然它们比我们最大的行星木星大多了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}While they're more massive than our largest planet, Jupiter...
Dialogue: 0,0:32:03.88,0:32:07.46,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,但是它们太昏暗了 望远镜都很难发现\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}they are so faint, telescopes have trouble detecting them.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:13.30,0:32:15.55,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,褐矮星是失败之星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}A brown dwarf is a failed star.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:15.60,0:32:16.89,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,它是自残者\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}lt's a wannabe.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:16.93,0:32:19.89,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,它是一个从未完全形成的气球\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}lt's a ball of gas that never quite made it.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:19.93,0:32:21.48,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,你要有一定量的气体\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}You have to have a certain amount of gas...
Dialogue: 0,0:32:21.52,0:32:25.69,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,然后才能燃烧 才能出现一个美丽的恒星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}before you get ignition and you get a beautiful star emerging.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:25.73,0:32:27.61,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,褐矮星就没有做到\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}A brown dwarf just didn't make it.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:29.98,0:32:32.49,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,尽管 没有成功成为恒星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Despite being a failure as a star...
Dialogue: 0,0:32:32.53,0:32:35.20,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,但是 褐矮星的温度依然相当可观\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}temperatures on brown dwarfs are still pretty impressive...
Dialogue: 0,0:32:38.03,0:32:40.62,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,达到了3000华氏度\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}at over 3,000 degrees Fahrenheit.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:42.96,0:32:46.00,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,不同于恒星会热到产生天气\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And unlike stars that are too hot to have weather...
Dialogue: 0,0:32:46.04,0:32:50.96,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,褐矮星会冷到足以经历对流和冷凝\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}brown dwarfs have cooled enough...to experience convection and condensation.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:53.05,0:32:54.30,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,在那样的温度下\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}At these temperatures...
Dialogue: 0,0:32:54.34,0:32:57.39,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,降雨具有全新的可怕含义\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}rain takes on a whole new terrifying meaning.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:02.60,0:33:04.43,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,褐矮星的大气层深处\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Deep in the atmosphere of a brown dwarf...
Dialogue: 0,0:33:04.48,0:33:06.85,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,温度高到铁都成了蒸汽了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}it's so hot that even iron is a vapor.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:06.90,0:33:09.40,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,那种气就像是地球大气层里的水\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}lt's a gas like water is in our own atmosphere.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:14.53,0:33:19.57,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,铁蒸汽上升 冷却凝固 变成了沙子\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}As iron vapors rise up, they cool, solidify, and turn to sand.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:22.37,0:33:24.41,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,铁会凝结起来\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The iron would start to condense...
Dialogue: 0,0:33:24.46,0:33:27.00,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,你就看到了云 大团的云\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and you have clouds, big, puffy clouds...
Dialogue: 0,0:33:27.04,0:33:30.75,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,只是这云是沙粒 滚烫 温度达到1500度\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}except the clouds would be sand, boiling hot, 1,500 degrees.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:30.80,0:33:32.50,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,因为在褐矮星上\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Because in a brown dwarf...
Dialogue: 0,0:33:32.55,0:33:34.01,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,你可以看到木星般大小的东西\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}you have something the size of Jupiter...
Dialogue: 0,0:33:34.05,0:33:37.80,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,然而 却囊括了木星30 40 甚至50倍的质量\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}but you've packed in 30 or40 or 50 times the mass of Jupiter...
Dialogue: 0,0:33:37.84,0:33:39.39,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,所以引力非常强\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the gravity is very high.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:39.43,0:33:42.35,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,其引力是地球的300倍\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}lt could be as high as 300 times the gravitywe have on Earth...
Dialogue: 0,0:33:42.39,0:33:44.39,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,因此 物体的坠落要快得多\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and so things can fall a lot faster.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:48.44,0:33:50.40,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,喷砂机的高速运动\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The highest moving velocity of a sandblaster...
Dialogue: 0,0:33:50.44,0:33:53.48,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,对于褐矮星上的沙粒来说一点都不为过\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}makes it a pretty good analogy for sand in a brown dwarf.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:54.82,0:33:56.78,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,在褐矮星的大气层里\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}ln the atmosphere of a brown dwarf...
Dialogue: 0,0:33:56.82,0:34:00.24,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,引力是地球的300倍\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the gravity is 300 times what it is here on Earth...
Dialogue: 0,0:34:00.28,0:34:06.16,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,云层里的小沙粒会以时速70 80甚至100英里落下\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and these little sand grains in the cloud would be falling...at 70, 80, or100 miles an hour.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:06.21,0:34:09.79,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,非常像喷砂机喷出的沙子\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}lt would be a lot like the sand coming out of this sandblaster.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:09.83,0:34:14.92,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,这块不锈钢板被喷砂机的力道给扭曲了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}This sheet of stainless steel has been warped...by the force of the sandblaster.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:14.96,0:34:19.63,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,你可以想象褐矮星大气层里的铁雨\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}You can imagine the iron rain in the atmosphere of a brown dwarf...
Dialogue: 0,0:34:19.68,0:34:21.72,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,以每小时上百英里降下\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}coming down at a hundred miles an hour...
Dialogue: 0,0:34:21.76,0:34:24.39,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,其结果就像这块钢板\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}what it might do to a sheet like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:26.48,0:34:27.98,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,这些液态铁雨滴\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}These drops of liquid iron...
Dialogue: 0,0:34:28.02,0:34:30.98,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,可能会有2800度 甚至3000华氏度\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}they may be 2,800, almost 3,000 degrees Fahrenheit...
Dialogue: 0,0:34:31.02,0:34:33.69,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,这些雨滴实际上落下的速度很高\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}these drops can really start falling at high velocity...
Dialogue: 0,0:34:33.73,0:34:35.61,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,时速50 80 甚至上百英里\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}fifty, eighty, a hundred miles an hour.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:35.65,0:34:38.32,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,所以你可以想象出你的雨伞会\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}So you can imagine your umbrella would be torn to shreds...
Dialogue: 0,0:34:38.36,0:34:40.74,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,被这融化的铁冰雹砸得粉碎\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}by this hail of molten iron.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:40.78,0:34:43.08,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,那将会是炼狱里的暴风雨\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}lt would be a real rainstorm from hell.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:46.66,0:34:49.41,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,这成了宇宙中最糟糕的天气\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}This has got to be the worst weather in the universe.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:54.63,0:35:01.84,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,热 对流 冷凝 - 天气要素\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Heat, convection, condensation... the elements ofweather.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:01.89,0:35:05.31,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,随便哪个 都会造成其它星球上的豪雨\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Alone, they cause spectacular rains...
Dialogue: 0,0:35:05.35,0:35:09.98,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,狂风和热浪\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}supersonic winds, and heat on other planets.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:10.02,0:35:13.40,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,它们结合在一起 就会形成难以想象的风暴\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Combine them, and incredible storms are formed.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:22.70,0:35:25.08,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,风暴需要温差\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}A storm needs a temperature difference.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:27.91,0:35:32.87,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,在地球上 每个风暴都是太阳不均匀加热导致的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}On Earth, every storm is a result of uneven heating by the Sun.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:35.13,0:35:39.21,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,最简单的例子就是海洋要比陆地来的冷\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The easiest example is the ocean is colder than the land.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:44.97,0:35:49.89,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,飓风 龙卷风 旋风\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Hurricanes, cyclones, and vortexes...
Dialogue: 0,0:35:49.93,0:35:52.60,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,是地球上天气的集大成者\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}are the great wonders ofweather on Earth...
Dialogue: 0,0:35:56.94,0:35:59.23,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,太空中也一样\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}but also in space.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:05.91,0:36:11.00,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,不同于地球上的风暴持续几小时或几天\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And unlike Earth, where storms last hours or perhaps a few days...
Dialogue: 0,0:36:11.04,0:36:15.38,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,太空中的某些风暴可以持续数百年\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}some storms in space can last centuries.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:15.42,0:36:17.92,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,那些飓风将使我们地球上的飓风\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}These hurricanes would make our hurricanes on Earth...
Dialogue: 0,0:36:17.96,0:36:19.30,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,看上去就像是夏季的习习凉风\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}look like a summer breeze.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:33.94,0:36:37.77,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,海王星具有太阳系里最快的风\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Neptune has the fastest winds in the solar system.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:41.11,0:36:44.36,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,然而 它也具有一个大暗斑\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But it also has a Great Dark Spot...
Dialogue: 0,0:36:44.41,0:36:47.03,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,一个神秘的飓风般的风暴\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}a mysterious hurricane-like storm...
Dialogue: 0,0:36:47.07,0:36:49.99,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,出没无常\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that appears and disappears with no warning.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:52.79,0:36:55.92,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,它围绕星球逆时针旋转\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}lt flies around the planet counterclockwise.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:58.96,0:37:00.80,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,旅行者2号发现\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Discovered byVoyager ll...
Dialogue: 0,0:37:00.84,0:37:03.80,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,它庞大 表现为黑色\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}it's big with black and blue features.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:05.55,0:37:10.14,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,其强烈的风暴如地球般大小\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}lt appears to be a fierce storm about the size of Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:12.43,0:37:15.39,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,科学家尚不清楚其形成的原因\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Scientists don't know what causes it to form...
Dialogue: 0,0:37:15.44,0:37:16.56,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,或为何它是黑色的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}orwhy it is black.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:19.19,0:37:23.07,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,它如太阳系里另一个风暴那样神秘\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}lt's a mystery...like another storm in our solar system.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:35.25,0:37:38.63,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,土星以其壮观的光环闻名遐迩\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Saturn is famous for its magnificent rings...
Dialogue: 0,0:37:38.67,0:37:42.75,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,但是提起它的大气层就有那么一点神秘了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}but is a little mysterious when it comes to its atmosphere.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:42.80,0:37:45.13,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,然而坐等30年\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But sit back and wait thirty years...
Dialogue: 0,0:37:45.17,0:37:48.09,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,土星就会出现一个异常壮观的风暴\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and Saturn will put on a storm so magnificent...
Dialogue: 0,0:37:48.14,0:37:50.68,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,会给其母亲星球留下深刻的印记\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}it would impress Mother Nature herself.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:03.78,0:38:05.99,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,它称为大白斑\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}lt's called the Great White Spot...
Dialogue: 0,0:38:06.03,0:38:10.82,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,每30年就在土星表面形成的巨大风暴\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}a gigantic storm that develops every thirty years on Saturn's surface...
Dialogue: 0,0:38:10.87,0:38:13.87,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,最终覆盖整个赤道地区\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}eventually covering the entire equator.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:15.41,0:38:17.58,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,这真是个行星级的现象\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}lt is truly a planetary-scale phenomenon...
Dialogue: 0,0:38:17.62,0:38:20.75,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,我们认为这是个极其可怕的雷暴\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and we think it's a monstrous, monstrous thunderstorm.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:23.84,0:38:27.97,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,科学家观察到了在土星赤道发展的风暴\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Scientists have observed the storm developing at Saturn's equator...
Dialogue: 0,0:38:28.01,0:38:30.76,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,那里接收到大部分太阳发出的热量\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}where it receives the most heat from the Sun.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:30.80,0:38:32.72,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,也许热量随着时间推移聚集起来\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Perhaps, heat builds over time...
Dialogue: 0,0:38:32.76,0:38:35.93,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,最终在星球上爆发成风暴\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and finally bursts into a storm on a planet...
Dialogue: 0,0:38:35.98,0:38:39.44,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,那里没有地表和摩擦使其速度降下来\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that has no surface orfriction to slow it down.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:39.48,0:38:41.73,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,也就是说 就好像是恶性循环\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}ln otherwords, it's sort of like a vicious circle...
Dialogue: 0,0:38:41.77,0:38:45.65,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,就好像 一旦你将球滚起来 一路滚下山\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}where, once you get the ball rolling, itjust rolls down the hill...
Dialogue: 0,0:38:45.69,0:38:47.24,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,风暴席卷全球\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and, you know, the storm goes global.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:48.74,0:38:51.45,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,几个月后 风暴的能量耗尽\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Months later, the storm runs out of energy...
Dialogue: 0,0:38:51.49,0:38:54.58,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,只得再潜伏30年\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}only to lie dormant for another thirty years.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:58.04,0:39:00.37,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,原因及时间尺度意味着什么\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}What the cause or time scale means...
Dialogue: 0,0:39:00.42,0:39:02.42,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,科学家确实不清楚\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}scientists truly don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:05.63,0:39:10.84,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,但是 土星的大白斑并不如我们太阳系里\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But Saturn's Great White Spot is not as powerful or everlasting...
Dialogue: 0,0:39:10.89,0:39:13.89,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,最大的风暴那样强大和永恒\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}as our biggest storm in the solar system.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:26.23,0:39:30.24,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,木星一直是科学遐想的源泉\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Jupiter has long been a source offascination for scientists...
Dialogue: 0,0:39:30.28,0:39:32.28,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,只要研究起太空中的狂野天气\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}when studying wild weather in space...
Dialogue: 0,0:39:33.28,0:39:37.62,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,其大风暴数百年来一直是大饱眼福的景色\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and its great storm has been a feast for the eyes for centuries.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:47.09,0:39:49.67,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,木星是太阳系里的巨人\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Jupiter is the giant of our solar system...
Dialogue: 0,0:39:49.72,0:39:52.88,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,让其他行星都相形见绌\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}dwarfing all other planets...
Dialogue: 0,0:39:52.93,0:39:55.93,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,因此 唯一与之适应的天气也成为了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}so it's only fitting its weather also becomes a showpiece...
Dialogue: 0,0:39:55.97,0:39:58.77,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,强大的力量和惊人的规模的典范\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}of sheer force and incredible size.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:07.02,0:40:10.32,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,1664年 天文学家罗伯特·胡克\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}ln 1664, the astronomer Robert Hooke...
Dialogue: 0,0:40:10.36,0:40:12.86,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,注意到了木星的一些怪异之处\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}noticed something strange about Jupiter.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:12.91,0:40:16.83,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,那里有个疙瘩 现在我们将其称为大红斑\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}There was a pimple there, which we now call the Great Red Spot.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:16.87,0:40:18.45,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,它一直固定不变\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}lt's been stable.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:18.49,0:40:24.46,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,想想看 一个数倍于地球的星际风暴\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Think of it, a planetary storm several times the size of the Earth...
Dialogue: 0,0:40:24.50,0:40:26.46,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,1664年以来没什么变化\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}stable since 1664.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:26.50,0:40:29.80,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,这是我们太阳系惊人的特征之一\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}This is one of the amazing features of our solar system.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:32.68,0:40:36.72,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,大红斑点的命名之后很久我们才知道那是什么\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The Great Red Spot was named that...long before we knew what it was...
Dialogue: 0,0:40:36.76,0:40:39.10,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,因为 你已经可以从地球上的望远镜看到它了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}because you can see it from a telescope on Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:39.14,0:40:40.72,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,因此数百年来\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And so for hundreds ofyears...
Dialogue: 0,0:40:40.77,0:40:42.93,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,人们已经了解了这个大红斑了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}people have known about this Great Red Spot.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:42.98,0:40:47.86,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,大红斑是太阳系里最引人注目的风暴\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The Great Red Spot...is the most impressive storm of our solar system...
Dialogue: 0,0:40:47.90,0:40:52.36,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,至少 在300年里一直在扰动\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and it's been churning for at least 300 years.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:52.40,0:40:54.32,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,我们太阳系里所有飓风的大妈\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The mother of all hurricanes in our solar system...
Dialogue: 0,0:40:54.36,0:40:55.49,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,其实实在木星上\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}is actually on Jupiter.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:55.53,0:40:56.99,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,严格说它并非飓风\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}lt's not technically a hurricane...
Dialogue: 0,0:40:57.03,0:40:59.12,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,然而 其行为举止非常像飓风\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}but it behaves very much like one.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:02.79,0:41:05.33,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,它具有热源 具有旋转的风\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}lt has a heat source, it has swirling winds...
Dialogue: 0,0:41:05.37,0:41:07.50,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,它让我们地球上的一切都相形见绌\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and it dwarfs anything on our planet.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:07.54,0:41:09.38,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,这个风暴非常巨大 你可以将两个地球\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}This storm is so big, you could take two Earths...
Dialogue: 0,0:41:09.42,0:41:11.84,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,塞进这个风暴的里头\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and stick them right inside of the storm.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:11.88,0:41:14.72,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,狂风肆作 时速达300英里\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The winds are blowing at 300 miles an hour.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:22.77,0:41:26.35,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,飓风和大红斑都是巨大的漩涡\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Both hurricanes and the Great Red Spot are giant vortices.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:26.40,0:41:28.77,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,对于飓风来说 它们是低压中心\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}ln the case of hurricanes, they're a low-pressure center.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:28.81,0:41:30.73,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,而大红斑则是高压中心\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The Great Red Spot is a high-pressure center.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:30.77,0:41:34.11,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,两者 都有高速风盘旋在漩涡中\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}ln both cases, there are high-speed winds circling the vortex.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:42.12,0:41:46.62,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,像一个大眼睛 风暴始终围绕着木星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Like a giant eye, the storm continuously circles Jupiter.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:47.46,0:41:50.84,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,风速达到时速400英里\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Wind speeds reach 400 miles per hour...
Dialogue: 0,0:41:50.88,0:41:54.88,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,大红斑从不显出会减小其强度\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and the giant red spot never seems to dwindle in strength.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:54.92,0:41:57.59,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,动力来自木星内部的热量\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Powered by the internal heat of Jupiter...
Dialogue: 0,0:41:57.64,0:42:00.26,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,它还吞噬着挡道的一切\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}it also eats anything in its path.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:00.30,0:42:01.93,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,如果你是个小漩涡\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}lfyou're a small vortex...
Dialogue: 0,0:42:01.97,0:42:04.60,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,处在大红斑的路径上 你要小心了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and you're in the path of the Great Red Spot, look out.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:04.64,0:42:06.77,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,你将会像小鱼那样被吃掉\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}You're going to be gobbled up like a little fish.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:10.44,0:42:13.65,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,科学家认为木星缺少地表和摩擦\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Scientists believe the lack offriction or surface on Jupiter...
Dialogue: 0,0:42:13.69,0:42:17.53,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,有可能让这个风暴在未来数百年间扰动不停\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}might allow this storm to churn uninterrupted for centuries more.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:24.95,0:42:26.75,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,在地球上 因为飓风打击大地时伴随很强的摩擦\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}On Earth, because of the strong friction...
Dialogue: 0,0:42:26.79,0:42:31.33,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,短短几天就会解体\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}when hurricanes hit land...they tend to fall apart in just a few days.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:31.38,0:42:35.30,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,另一方面 大红斑的寿命会超过百年\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}On the other hand, the Great Red Spot...has a lifetime of over a hundred years.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:35.34,0:42:37.22,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,我们确实不明白其中的细节\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}We don't really understand this in detail...
Dialogue: 0,0:42:37.26,0:42:40.80,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,但是 有可能这意味着木星大气层里的摩擦\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}but it probably it means that the friction...in Jupiter's atmosphere
Dialogue: 0,0:42:40.84,0:42:42.35,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,相对地球的大气层 非常的弱\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}is very weak...compared to in Earth's atmosphere.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:43.60,0:42:47.39,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,木星是行星的一个很好的例子 即行星本身\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Jupiter is a good example of a planet where the planet itself...
Dialogue: 0,0:42:47.43,0:42:49.94,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,至少能提供部分能量\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}is what's supplying at least some of the energy...
Dialogue: 0,0:42:49.98,0:42:53.48,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,来驾驭风暴持续数百年\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to drive a storm that's lasting for centuries.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:01.66,0:43:04.16,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,天气… 大气的状态\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Weather...the state of an atmosphere.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:04.20,0:43:05.95,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,纵贯宇宙\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Throughout the universe...
Dialogue: 0,0:43:06.00,0:43:12.21,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,类似地球上的天气事件在其他行星上精彩上演\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}familiarweather events on Earth are played out...in fantastic ways on other planets.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:14.42,0:43:17.42,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,那么 为何要研究其他行星上的天气呢？\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But why study weather on other planets at all?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:19.38,0:43:23.76,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,假如你只是就地球研究地球的话\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}lfyou only ever study Earth...for examples to understand Earth...
Dialogue: 0,0:43:24.64,0:43:27.22,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,你就可能错失这些现象更为广泛的背景\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}you may be missing a much broader context...in which the phenomenon...
Dialogue: 0,0:43:27.27,0:43:30.98,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,那是你描述所无法割裂的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that you're trying to describe is imbedded.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:31.02,0:43:32.15,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,比如 我们观察地球\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}So, for example, we look at Earth...
Dialogue: 0,0:43:32.19,0:43:33.86,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,我们讨论温室效应\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and we talk about a greenhouse effect.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:34.86,0:43:36.69,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,你要认识它 就必须去瞧一瞧\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}You want to learn about it, go check it out.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:36.73,0:43:37.78,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,观察金星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Look atVenus.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:39.65,0:43:42.07,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,一厢情愿地认为你解决地球上问题的所有办法\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The urge is to believe that all your solutions...
Dialogue: 0,0:43:42.11,0:43:46.45,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,只能通过观察地球来得到\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to your problems on Earth can be found by only looking at Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:46.99,0:43:50.16,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,那是短视的 近乎痴人说梦\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}That is shortsighted, bordering on delusional.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:52.92,0:43:55.75,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,我们在研究陌生的环境中熟悉的过程时\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}When we study familiar processes in unfamiliar settings...
Dialogue: 0,0:43:55.79,0:43:58.55,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,那真是在考验我们是否明白发生了什么\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}it really tests whether or not we understand what's happening.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:01.38,0:44:04.64,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,对于其他行星上生命存在的可能性\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}ln terms of the possibility of life on other planets...
Dialogue: 0,0:44:04.68,0:44:07.26,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,了解其天气状况绝对是关键所在\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}understanding the weather patterns is absolutely key.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:08.18,0:44:09.35,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,我们是众多行星中的一个\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}We're one planet of many.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:09.39,0:44:11.73,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,太阳是众多恒星中的一个\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The Sun is one star of many.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:11.77,0:44:14.52,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,我们处在星系极其普通的部分\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}We're in an undistinguished part of the galaxy.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:14.56,0:44:18.07,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,有许多需要通过探索别人的意见来加以认识\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}There's much to be learned by exploring what others say.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:18.30,0:44:26.30,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,谢谢观赏\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Thanks For Viewing
